snippet.textDisplay: We don’t have a centralized healthcare system in Spain. We have independent administrations in our autonomous regions, similarly as your States do with many administrative matters. The budget is centralized and distributed to the regions. The management is partially decentralized. Not as much as it should be, but it is quite so
